{
  "doc_id": "57590",
  "text": "Within the Baylisascaris genus, phylogenetic relationships have been investigated using several molecular targets (i.e., numerous mitochondrial genes, nuclear 5.8S, and second internal transcribed spacer (ITS-2) rDNA sequences). The three ursid-specific Baylisascaris species (B. transfuga, B. ailuri and B. schroederi) are more closely related to each other than to B. procyonis and B. ailuri is more similar to B. transfuga than to B. schroederi [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Evidence from nuclear 5.8S and ITS-2 rDNA sequences also showed higher genetic similarity between B. transfuga and B. schroederi compared to B. procyonis [CITATION_4] .",
